de.jannlab.core

Class CellArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.jannlab.core.CellArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class CellArray
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A CellArray defines a range of cells with the same functional specification and same computation-point-of-time. Semantically the computation-point-of-time can be considered as parallel for cells in the array.

    Author:
    Sebastian Otte
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • layer

        public int layer
        Refers the parent layer.

      • compidx

        public int compidx
        Defines the computation-point-of-time in the corresponding layer. If the value is -1 this indicates that the CellArray contains non-computing cells.

      • ilctag

        public int ilctag
        This tag can be one of ILC_IN, ILC_OUT or ILC_BOTH. It indicates the "connective-type" of the cells. This allows to define input, output and "hidden" cells per layer.
